What happened in this case? The web hostâ€™s DNS server went down and it had a cascading sort of effect. It affected their mail services as well since they were hosting their own mail servers. Needless to say, this incident left a bad impression on their customer who is now looking out for a better provider.
 
This can happen to any hosting provider or organization. A failure of the DNS service can trigger a failure of the interconnected parts. Multiple services such as websites, mail servers, proxy servers, etc. can be affected. 
 
